    <section id="faq">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="section-head">
          <h2>FAQ</h2>
          <p>Educators, students, and procurement — including questions we hear in UK &amp; UAE conversations.</p>
        </div>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Who is FairShare for?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">Higher education, sixth form / college, and high school group work where you want clearer coordination and fairer visibility into contributions — without replacing your LMS overnight.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Does FairShare replace our LMS?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">No. FairShare focuses on <em>group project execution</em> — tasks, docs, chat, and contribution signals. Most institutions keep Moodle, Canvas, Blackboard, or Google Classroom for modules, submission, and grades.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do you handle UK GDPR?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">We document our role (often processor to your institution), list subprocessors, support Data Processing Agreements, and describe retention and security on our <a href="security.html">Security &amp; trust</a> page. Your DPO validates fit for your school.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What about UAE PDPL and cross-border transfers?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">Institutions in the UAE should assess transfers (e.g. UK/EU hosting or AI subprocessors) under PDPL rules. We provide information for your transfer analysis; legal sign-off sits with your organisation.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is student data safe?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">Run FairShare on a properly configured host, use strong authentication, and follow our security documentation. We do not market FairShare as a consumer toy — it is intended for institutional use with appropriate governance.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What does “contribution analytics” mean?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">Signals from activity and tasks — useful for coaching and spotting imbalance. They are not proof of misconduct; instructors remain responsible for academic judgment.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>SSO and school domains?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">Campus-tier customers can discuss SSO and domain allowlists as part of procurement. Roadmap items are confirmed in writing — not promised on this marketing page alone.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can we export data if we leave?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">Institutional contracts should define export and deletion windows. The product includes export paths for key artefacts; confirm scope with sales for Campus agreements.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do we get started?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">Book a demo, run a Starter pilot with one cohort, then move to Team or Campus when procurement and safeguarding sign-off are in place.</div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>

